WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:19.426
Question: can the same physics clues rank bacteria risk on a beach the model has never trained on?

00:00:19.426 --> 00:00:36.833
Target: enterococcus above 104, a high-bacteria beach-water warning line.

00:00:36.833 --> 00:00:56.880
Clean inputs: sun, rain, wind, heat, and flushing. No beach names or lab history.

00:00:56.880 --> 00:01:14.241
Fair test: hide a whole basin, train elsewhere, then rank the hidden basin.

00:01:14.241 --> 00:01:30.608
Result: useful cold-start FIB ranking, not just random chance.

00:01:30.608 --> 00:01:49.024
Catch: local history usually wins after a beach has enough samples.

00:01:49.024 --> 00:02:10.100
Negative controls failed: hypoxia and domoic acid are not explained by the FIB recipe.

00:02:10.100 --> 00:02:27.087
Bottom line: real cold-start FIB ranking, not a universal ocean brain.
